  "doc_id": "2010",
  "text": "In addition to the extrinsic pathway and the intrinsic pathway, there also exists caspaseindependent pathway. This pathway relies on apoptosis-inducing factors (AIFs). AIFs are flavoproteins present in the inner mitochondrial membrane [CITATION_1] , and exhibit the pro-apoptosis effect. AIFs are released into cytoplasm along with the increased permeability or the cleavage of mitochondria. Then, AIFs enter the nucleus and lead to chromatin condensation and break into fragments. Polster has studied the relationship of AIFs and mitochondrial ROS production [CITATION_2] . Insufficient AIF would reduce the electron transport chain complex I, which relates to chronic neurodegeneration [CITATION_3] .",
